    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-03-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-03-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <head>No. 611.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Heap</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-03-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 5, 1880</date>. (Received March
                        29.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 2.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Lieutenant-Colonel Kummeran, the military attaché
                    of the Russian embassy, whilst riding with Mr. Onou, the Russian chargé
                    d’affaires, on the 27th of February, in the vicinity of Pera, was fired at by a
                    Bosnian Mahometan and wounded in two places. He died on the 3d instant and was
                    buried yesterday afternoon.</p>
                <p>The funeral was attended by the diplomatic corps in uniform, a battalion of the
                    imperial guard with the Sultan’s military band, the crews of the Russian and
                    Austrian stationaires and a following of some 10,000 persons.</p>
                <p>The assassin was arrested, with his two companions. He offered a desperate
                    resistance and was severely wounded in the struggle.</p>
                <p>This incident, which is attributed to a plot of the Nihilists, has occasioned
                    some excitement, as it is supposed that it was the intention to shoot Mr. Onou,
                    who indeed had a narrow escape, a ball having passed through his coat.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>G. H. HEAP,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
